TITLE: Using Controlled State with Required State Property in Qwik
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates that when using onStateChange callbacks, you must provide the corresponding state value in the state option. Without this, the state will remain frozen at its initial value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TanStack/table/blob/main/docs/framework/qwik/guide/table-state.md#2025-04-19_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
const sorting = Qwik.useSignal([])
//...
const table = useQwikTable({
  columns,
  data,
  //...
  state: {
    sorting: sorting.value, //required because we are using `onSortingChange`
  },
  onSortingChange: updater => {
    sorting.value = updater instanceof Function ? updater(sorting) : updater //makes the `state.sorting` controlled
  }, 
})
```

